[[fr:Carrelage de Frames]]

'''This page is part of the description of OneOnOneEmacs.

You can tile the visible [[frame]]s either horizontally
or vertically: `tile-frames-horizontally' or
`tile-frames-vertically'.  One use of this feature is for comparing or merging [[buffer]]s using '''ediff''' commands.

Here's a screenshot showing comparison using `ediff' of two buffers in frames that are tiled horizontally: 

[[image:DrewsEmacsTileSS]]

'''See Library:''' <tt>[[frame-cmds.el]]</tt>.  It also has other frame commands, such as commands to maximize and restore (toggle maximize) in different directions.

'''See Also:''' FisheyeWithThumbs for tiling frame thumbnails.

----
OneOnOneEmacs CategoryFrames FrameModes CategoryDisplay
